Get to Know Service Cloud Voice
Improve phone support with Service Cloud Voice. Service Cloud Voice is completely integrated into Salesforce, providing a consistent experience for agents, supervisors, and customers across all digital channels.

Set Up Service Cloud Voice
Get up and running with Service Cloud Voice. Before you start, review the Voice prerequisites, limitations, and planning resources.

Customize Service Cloud Voice
You have successfully completed all the necessary setup tasks, and Service Cloud Voice is now operational. While it is not mandatory, you have the option to customize Service Cloud Voice further, unlocking advanced capabilities that can significantly enhance the overall experience for your customers, agents, and supervisors.

Test Service Cloud Voice
As you roll Service Cloud Voice out to your users, run tests and try Service Cloud Voice in a sandbox.

Monitor Your Contact Center
Monitor the performance of your Service Cloud Voice contact center.
Track And Report On Your Amazon Connect Usage and Billing
Track your Amazon Connect usage to stay on top of your billing for Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect. Understand how you’re billed for minutes and IVR utterances.

Maintain Your Contact Center
Keep your contact center running optimally. Use the latest version of contact center components and, as needed, delete customers’ personal identifiable information (PII) from your Service Cloud Voice contact center.

Supervise and Train Agents on Service Cloud Voice
Train and monitor your Service Cloud Voice agents.
Help Customers on the Phone
Talk to your customers using Service Cloud Voice. Answer incoming calls and make outbound calls in Service Cloud. Collaborate with your colleagues in the call record’s Chatter feed by posting call updates, asking questions, and discussing next steps.

Get Expert Support for Service Cloud Voice
Get help with Voice directly from the experts. If you need assistance, find out whether it’s best to contact Salesforce Support or your telephony provider.

Amazon Connect Reference for Service Cloud Voice
If you use Amazon Connect as your telephony provider, Service Cloud Voice uses Amazon Connect components to manage and route calls in your contact center. To understand how Service Cloud uses Amazon Connect, review these resources.
